commit_message:
Test for both deletes in multiple delete test

The multiple volume delete tests test for deletion of volumes
"1234" and "5678", but only ensure that the delete operation is
called for the later.

Change-Id: I6224eef8c4186b5df82b085666a2605489faa714

commit_message:
Remove Python 3.3 from list of tox environments

Remove Python 3.3 from the list of tox test environments since we do
not currently support Python 3.3 for swift.

Change-Id: I7993a511e8433b21b292f21f4775e4ef2b5c2539

[{'created': '2013-11-30 13:38:17.000000000', 'message': 'Replace deprecated method assertEquals

TestCase.assertEquals is deprecated since Python 2.7, so need use new
method name assertEqual.
See http://docs.python.org/2/library/unittest.html#deprecated-aliases

Change-Id: Iae9074f2afe2a572b60f6192aa6c871db42360ec
'}]
commit_message:
Replace deprecated method assertEquals

TestCase.assertEquals is deprecated since Python 2.7, so need use new
method name assertEqual.
See http://docs.python.org/2/library/unittest.html#deprecated-aliases

Change-Id: Iae9074f2afe2a572b60f6192aa6c871db42360ec

commit_message:
Don't overwrite marker when checking if it exists

Checking for the existence of a marker overwrote which marker was being
checked for.  The string representation of the marker needs to be
retained so that a proper exception can be built.  So a new variable is
introduced which can be used to check for marker existence.

Change-Id: I81cfdceca3921c364cdeeccd24add14a6b1d0fd4
Closes-bug: 1257008

commit_message:
Fixing console auth service and process names for RHEL.

vncproxy_console_auth process and service names are incorrect
for RHEL. Also, added vncproxy_console_packages, process and
service name.

Closes-bug: #1256456

revisions:
[{'created': '2013-12-02 00:54:43.000000000', 'message': 'Multiple testing fixes

* Changes NotificationHandler base to be a object and the tests to inherit it
  like a mixin, test_invalid method fails if not due to duplicate test id.
* Changes backend tests to use scenarios and special NSD4 tests puts the setUp
  logic into a fixture which is loaded for the NSD4 backend tests.
* Remove any get_*_service call into start_service(name) which uses a fixture
  ServiceFixture that automatically cleans up the service upon teardown (no

commit_message:
Multiple testing fixes

* Changes NotificationHandler base to be a object and the tests to inherit it
  like a mixin, test_invalid method fails if not due to duplicate test id.
* Changes backend tests to use scenarios and special NSD4 tests puts the setUp
  logic into a fixture which is loaded for the NSD4 backend tests.
* Remove any get_*_service call into start_service(name) which uses a fixture
  ServiceFixture that automatically cleans up the service upon teardown (no
  more sprinkling tearDowns all over the tests to stop a service).
* Use fixture for database. Removes storage.setup_schema and teardown_schema.
* Fix cleanup of notifications.
* Use fixture for Policy instead of in teardown().

bug #1256728

Change-Id: I72a53eed9e81d3f014015aa443582de21a4e66ee

commit_message:
Add ML2 plugin support

This patch aims to support:
- ml2 configuration for Open-vSwitch & Linux Bridge plugins
- mechanism drivers: flat, gre, vlan vxlan
- l2 population support for OVS & linux bridge plugins

implement blueprint ml2-support
Cherry-picked from https://review.openstack.org/#/c/48289/

Change-Id: I9a4224f899e95411c509f583bf04dfc4dd0de25b
Signed-off-by: Emilien Macchi <emilien.macchi@enovance.com>

commit_message:
feat(health): make health API storage-aware

This change makes the GET request of /health to ensure that all
connected storage shards accepts `ping` command before responding
200; otherwise, 503.

The HEAD request is unchanged.

Closes-Bug: 1243268
Change-Id: I75c3b46ccb1a5a66e6c12766d3e451fd3478822c

commit_message:
Don't call credentials_headers() twice

We don't need to call credentials_headers in the stack create/update
code, as it's already called in the HTTPClient.  This has the side-
effect of simplifying the shell test, which currently has to mock
header arguments to json_request, which are incorrect anyway because
HTTPClient always sets X-Auth-Token if a token is passed in (as
evidenced by bug #1250731)

Change-Id: I6212cf5a50f5a8d919f743e23ece4bd1d0e1ad1c
Partial-Bug: #1252248

commit_message:
feat(validation): verify project id length

Unlike Client-ID or queue name, project id is deployment-defined.
However, we can place a reasonable limit on the max length.

Change-Id: I3ebc3c9e04c7a5673083fb384ea6889e69045a99
Closes-Bug: 1233418

commit_message:
Remove extra www/api-ref-guides.html

This file is not referenced anywhere AFAIK, it gets published at
http://api.openstack.org/api-ref-guides.html

We do have in openstack-manuals a similar file that is referenced:
http://docs.openstack.org/api/api-ref-guides.html

Remove this extra version.

Change-Id: I2286bbfe2645ca84df928a8adebed7851a179ed4

strict dependency of the 7.0.x series. CHANGELOG cleanup.

commit_message:
centos-image-resize -> linux-rootfs-resize

The image guide links to an external project to build resizeable
virtual machine images. Its name changed from centos-image-resize
to linux-rootfs-resize.

Update the image guide to reflect this change.

Change-Id: I802530237aee91c110f9241497a0a2f0988e0c83

commit_message:
Relax the dependency on openstack-identity to the 7.x series

openstack-identity is now on 7.2.0, which doesn't get picked up because of the
strict dependency of the 7.0.x series.

Change-Id: If374c256fbe15d6bc5f4eb19fd800eacd87a0f7a

commit_message:
Remove conductor 1.X rpc api

A previous change adding support for the 2.x rpc interface but retained
compatibility with 1.x as a transition point.  This commit removes the
old API from the server side.

UpgradeImpact

Part of blueprint rpc-major-version-updates-icehouse

Change-Id: I0cf2a1c21990342ca41ddd2e11e373508a5e67c8

commit_message:
Remove scheduler 2.x rpc api

A previous change adding support for the 3.x rpc interface but retained
compatibility with 2.x as a transition point.  This commit removes the
old API from the server side.

The changes are mostly just removing lots of deprecated and now unused
code.

UpgradeImpact

Part of blueprint rpc-major-version-updates-icehouse

Change-Id: If96c8689ee62d4b01b5605c494115ba25353e660

Correct network_device_mtu help string

This patch corrects the network_device_mtu help string. This setting
changes the mtu size for the interface not the vlan.

commit_message:
Align projects list with mirror-needing projects

If projects.txt is going to be the basis for select-mirror in the
gate, we should also list projects in projects.txt that need to be
constrained by the mirror for their testing. In order to do that, we
need to not try to unconditionally update setup.py, since devstack and
devstack-gate do not have it.

openstack/requirements itself also does not use the mirror, so remove
it from the list.

commit_message:
Adding domain to context and log

Add support for upcoming "domain" concept in Keystone V3 API in
both logging and context.

Closes-Bug: #1248936
Implements: blueprint add-domain-info-to-context
Change-Id: Ic2cf3e52cfcc0b8adccdf9c59afaa4014708a303

commit_message:
Targeted graph flow pattern

This change adds graph flow like pattern that is able to ignore graph
nodes (not even add them to flow) if they are not needed to run certain
task.

Implements blueprint targeted-graph-flow
Change-Id: I57d5a1c0598bd032d77e2a262b2d9644418ce3f6

The reason I'm using RETURN is the case the packet goes from a VM to the other VM in the same host.

so let's say we have VM_A and VM_B
VM_B wanna refuse ping from anywhere.

VM_A pings to VM_B.
if we use ALLOW, the packet will reach VM_B because
it the patch may hit the iptables rule for VM_A first then ALLOWed immediately."}, {'account_id': 4656, 'date': '2013-11-07 09:52:56.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 5:

I have the same question as Nachi - I can't seem to get this to work either.

And I still don't think this change is correct as it will allow all Icmpv6 traffic through, when only a subset should be allowed.  I think the following should be allowed on the input side: RA, NS, and NA, and they should be inserted with a '-j RETURN'.

Also, can you double-check your default policy is to ACCEPT with 'ip6tables -L' ?  On one of my systems I had to tweak that with 'ip6tables -P FORWARD ACCEPT' (INPUT and OUTPUT possibly too), otherwise things don't flow.

Thanks."}, {'account_id': 4656, 'date': '2013-11-18 23:35:49.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 5:

Here's our ip6tables output:

http://paste.openstack.org/show/53144/"}, {'account_id': 1131, 'date': '2013-11-20 17:10:31.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 5:

Hi Sean,

I'm just trying to make sure I have the flow here correct.

On output from a tap, the packet should flow through iptables like so:

FORWARD -> neutron-openvswi-FORWARD -> neutron-openvswi-sg-chain -> neutron-openvswi-ifoobar

If that chain does a -j RETURN, it should get back to the FORWARD chain and use the default ACCEPT policy

On input to the other tap, it should:

FORWARD -> neutron-openvswi-FORWARD -> neutron-openvswi-sg-chain -> neutron-openvswi-ofoobar

If that has a rule to allow ipv6-icmp (with a -j RETURN), it should also get back to the FORWARD chain and use the default ACCEPT policy

If I could get this working enough to login to my instance, I'd kill my agent and start manipulating the rules by hand.

If you don't have that -j ACCEPT for ipv6-icmp, what rule is dropping the packets?  Is it the invalid state check since there's possibly a neighbour solicitation being sent?  Perhaps some of these rules need to be added with top=True?"}, {'account_id': 4656, 'date': '2013-11-25 15:15:20.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 5: Abandoned

The root cause is the usage of LibvirtHybridOVSBridgeDriver - which breaks IPv6 functionality. Changing to LibvirtGenericVIFDriver resolves the issue'}, {'account_id': 4656, 'date': '2013-11-27 04:32:01.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 5: Restored'}, {'account_id': 4656, 'date': '2013-11-27 04:32:37.000000000', 'content': 'Uploaded patch set 6.'}, {'account_id': 4656, 'date': '2013-11-27 04:37:02.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 6:

Changing from the Hybrid OVS VIF driver to the Generic VIF driver was a red herring - it actually broke security groups entirely which was allowing all traffic in, including ICMPv6 traffic. 

Please take a look at the types I am allowing inbound to an instance, it is currently types 130, 131, 132, 134, 136. Outbound is covered by the rules that were generated in _spoofing_rule, which allows all icmpv6 traffic outbound from the instance by default.'}, {'account_id': 4656, 'date': '2013-11-27 04:41:06.000000000', 'content': 'Uploaded patch set 7.'}, {'account_id': 4656, 'date': '2013-11-27 04:41:22.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 6:

commit_message:
Pass in certain ICMPv6 types by default

This allows instances to do SLAAC configuration, without requiring
explicit security group rules to do so.

Closes-Bug: #1242933

commit_message:
Cleanup ec2/metadata/osapi address/port listen config option help

Commit d88cfbd changed the help for the osapi_compute_listen_port config
option but the grammar could be cleaned up a bit for not only that
option but the ec2 and metadata API IP address/port listening options in
nova.service, so this patch cleans them all up.

Before this fix when test run was started and this test run must have
included tests that had been executed earlier with another test run
multiple copies for current test run were created which leads to
messed up ui. To avoid this query for tests from which copies will be
created was extended to provide correct results.

Change-Id: I8b9cca4c57ee973e4f818ecdc6079b24f108f555
'}]
commit_message:
Fix bug with test dublicationd for test run

Before this fix when test run was started and this test run must have
included tests that had been executed earlier with another test run
multiple copies for current test run were created which leads to
messed up ui. To avoid this query for tests from which copies will be
created was extended to provide correct results.

Change-Id: I8b9cca4c57ee973e4f818ecdc6079b24f108f555

commit_message:
Fn::Replace support for type Number

Currently Fn:Replace works just with type String:
{Fn:Replace [{'str': 'new_str'}, 'change str']}

After this fix it will work for type Number:
{Fn:Replace [{'str': 42}, 'change str']}

Change-Id: I709a3350b5676bd9db8bac92e07ad105466bd187
Closes-Bug: #1256326

commit_message:
Switch the base URL to git.openstack.org

The git repositories on github for openstack are mirrors of the primary
repositories, which are hosted on git.openstack.org, so switch as much
as I can to using the primary, rather than the github mirror.

Change-Id: Idcfda49a691582055256b830c61e098f4a271339

commit_message:
Add multi-worker support

Since https://review.openstack.org/#/c/37131/ got merged, Neutron
supports now multiple worker processes for API server.

Change-Id: Ib01240c39de21306892f4f92e0ba3ecb56837a7c
Signed-off-by: Emilien Macchi <emilien.macchi@enovance.com>

commit_message:
Adds new API for share metadata operating

Adds command 'metadata' for setting and unsetting metadata keys.
Adds command 'metadata-update-all' for updating all metadata.
Adds command 'metadata-show' for viewing share metadata.
Adds key '--metadata' to command 'create'

Partially implements bp manila-client-enhancements
Change-Id: I10d20e12e71065d6e40be062715fa01998828ab2

commit_message:
Adds an ability to manage share metadata

Now on share creating, we can specify metadata and it
will be saved in database. Also support of setting,
deleting and updating metadata info was added.

Adds model for share metadata
Adds migration
Adds api extension for share metadata
Adds relative api functions

Partially implements bp manila-client-enhancements
Change-Id: Id421323dd9e947d536b577092f1875f178d9aba5

commit_message:
Avoid "virsh net-destroy" on inactive bridge

If running "virsh net-destroy" on inactive bridge will get error:
error: Requested operation is not valid: network is not active

Change the logic to a simple&direct one to remove bridge.

Change-Id: Ie0341a1fc09c16c1b9427e847b9dbf9afd25f69e
Closes-Bug: #1256510

subject: adds NetworkInterfaces to LaunchConfiguration
messages:
[{'account_id': 7385, 'date': '2013-12-02 16:54:26.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 1: I would prefer that you didn't merge this

Presumably it's missing something? Nothings uses that property.

Regardless, we should be careful with modifications to AWS resources, ideally we wouldn't have those kind of extensions, and instead support the use case in a Openstack resource (though they don't exist yet in the autoscale case)."}, {'account_id': 7256, 'date': '2013-12-02 16:56:15.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 1: I would prefer that you didn't merge this

Agreed with Thomas. That being said, shouldn't this be handled by setting 'VPCZoneIdentifier' on the group which (I think) should assign the instances to a subnet?"}, {'account_id': 7730, 'date': '2013-12-02 16:57:39.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 1:

Yes you probably right.'}, {'account_id': 7730, 'date': '2013-12-02 16:58:10.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 1: Abandoned

We have to keep compatibility with Amazon Cloud Formation'}, {'account_id': 7730, 'date': '2013-12-02 17:06:09.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 1:

@Thomas Herve	

Actually nothing is missing, the workflow can easily handle this property https://github.com/openstack/heat/blob/master/heat/engine/resources/autoscaling.py#L221

But you right, we have to keep the compatibility with cloudformation:

http://docs.aws.amazon.com/AWSCloudFormation/latest/UserGuide/aws-properties-as-launchconfig.html'}, {'account_id': 7385, 'date': '2013-12-02 17:36:21.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 1:

I was more thinking in terms of tests. Presumably the network added in the configuration should be passed to a call somewhere.

Regarding the compatibility, we don't *have* to keep it, We already have incompatible bits, we just need to be careful about what we add. It'd be nice to rephrase your bug in term of use cases so that we know what's to be done."}]

commit_message:
Added empty packages and a test for the API v1

Created two packages in queues (api and api/v1)
added a api test to tests/unit/common. Also changed
the common/errors to include invalid operations
error used in test_api.

Change-Id: I32d7a2eebbde50e96cb49391b591c409e6ab6df2

commit_message:
use new package/service names to replace openvswitch

tested on rhels6.4, the package name openstack-quantum-openvswitch
replace the openstack-quantum-openvswitch-agent, and the service
name quantum-openvswitch-agent replace the old name for redhat and
centos. So I fixed it here.

Change-Id: I28730867f05cb5d4b310380c3307512b9e956f36
Closes-Bug: #1244563

Sharding need special storage driver wrapper for queue-related
operations. The listing queue algorithm merge the listing result
from multiple storage connections, and return them in sorted order.

storage connection, and the algorithms does not run asynchronously
yet (since there is no way to test).

commit_message:
feat(shard): queue listing from multiple sources

Sharding need special storage driver wrapper for queue-related
operations. The listing queue algorithm merges the listing result
from multiple storage connections, and return them in sorted order.

This patch also fixes non-configurable default limits in sharding.

Change-Id: If9bd80459bd1a0dc92ea68c42bc28c0f6dde2a65
Partitally-implements: blueprint storage-sharding

Thanks!"}, {'account_id': 1669, 'date': '2013-11-22 09:14:09.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 2:

Sure, I even wrote an article just for you:

http://julien.danjou.info/blog/2013/guide-python-static-class-abstract-methods

:-)

To summarize, the staticmethod decorator does not influence inheritance, it's only related to the actual implementation of the method. It influences how Python object "instantiator" will create a new bound method or not, that's all.'}, {'account_id': 4393, 'date': '2013-11-22 16:49:58.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 2: Looks good to me (core reviewer)

commit_message:
Bumping up max_length of flavor extra spec.

The capture field in the flavor extra spec form, is currently set to 25,
but should be bumped up to accommodate some long values.

Change-Id: I54a12b01222faf0d7dd32768c73f192e3d3cf8e1
Fixes: bug #1252427

commit_message:
Make flow operation parameters explicit

Changes the _build_flow_expr_arr() method to accept explicit keyword
arguments, rather than a **kwargs dict which needs to be validated.
For more info see the discussion on the related bug report.

Closes bug: 1240572

Change-Id: I143395b8e938b8b6dbefe30762b528d3c15581a9

commit_message:
Incorporating MIT licensed code

This patch attempts to clarify the licensing position
held by the db.sqlalchemy.migration module. According to
https://wiki.openstack.org/wiki/LegalIssuesFAQ when we have MIT licensed
code in the project we have to update the toplevel LICENSE file to include
the details of the license + a brief explanation of which code is under
that license.

This patch also fixes the license header on that module which was
incomplete.

Change-Id: I5675f3f6f63ac6432736a98e94fbe2cb3e32714f

commit_message:
Drop dependency on fileutils from oslo db tests

Module fileutils from openstack common requres common log.
We should avoid of use openstack common log module, because it
registers a few oslo.config options, so can possibly lead to
unpleasant issues (DuplicateOptError).

We used only fileutils.write_to_tempfile() function, from fileutils,
so it can be replaced to similar create_tempfiles() method from
BaseTestCase() class.

Related to blueprint oslo-db-lib

Change-Id: I25d97c877687a8b5e4343f5376e92ba269bca98a

commit_message:
Use log.warning() instead of log.warn() in oslo.db

Method warn() is provided by ContextAdapter from openstack common log
module. It is the same as logging.LoggerAdapter.warning(), so we can
easily replece it to warning().

It allows us drop dependency on log module from oslo db code.

Change-Id: I31fe047a8c71b2818c81dd6aa9cef96026c9b649

commit_message:
Add missing argument max_size in libvirt driver

max_size argument was added in commit 3cdfe894ab58f7b91bf7fb690fc5bc724e44066f,
but missing  in _create_ephemeral and _create_swap method, which cause
exception raised when caching ephemeral and swap disk files of the instance.

Add test for _create_ephemeral used with max_size parameter
and test _create_swap method

Closes-Bug: 1251152
Closes-Bug: 1250032
(cherry picked from commit 384f55bcb32251698cc2ce839a0286ef99e74984)

Conflicts:
	nova/tests/virt/libvirt/test_libvirt.py
	nova/virt/libvirt/driver.py

Change-Id: I46032ad32f317c923692b8b3d40cedd0dce06cad

commit_message:
Pass Instance object to spice compute rpc api

Update the get_spice_console() method of the compute rpc api to take in
an Instance object instead of a dict.  The object_compat() decorator is
used to maintain backwards compatibility with receiving a dict.

Change-Id: I0bafe18d9c8bffcd0b72629542fbf7aedacdfbb4

commit_message:
Run coverage tests with --concurrency=1 too

Due to various race conditions we've been running unit tests with
--concurrency=1 for a long time now. The same must be done to coverage
tests too.

Change-Id: Ie402ee005043e250ee5778a00efc16db588ed811
Closes-Bug: #1252743

Relax the dependency on openstack-identity to the 7.x series

openstack-identity is now on 7.2.0, which doesn't get picked up because of the
strict dependency of the 7.0.x series.

[{'created': '2013-11-27 12:02:01.000000000', 'message': 'Avoid eventlet-unsafe exception handling

Eventlet can context-switch during a log call (at least in principle).
Therefore it is unsafe to use "raise" after this call, because the exception
raised may not be the same one caught by the "except" block, but rather
could be any random exception from some other greenlet.

This is a canonical example of why eventlet is pure evil.

Fixes bug: #1255506

Change-Id: Ieb0eb763c0fd696b82212653ac4909d2bddf6b88
'}]
commit_message:
Avoid eventlet-unsafe exception handling

Eventlet can context-switch during a log call (at least in principle).
Therefore it is unsafe to use "raise" after this call, because the exception
raised may not be the same one caught by the "except" block, but rather
could be any random exception from some other greenlet.

This is a canonical example of why eventlet is pure evil.

Fixes bug: #1255506

Doh - hit publish too quickly ;-(

I wanted to add that I've moved a comment from the dependent patch to here.  I like the concept but don't see why in the context of Nova's control of VMs why bootable has to be an attribute of the virt driver.  It it was an instance attribute then we could have a common implementation just in the compute manager layer."}, {'account_id': 1501, 'date': '2013-11-24 08:47:26.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 8: (2 inline comments)

Sorry - I see now that this is going to be used for deleted instances and so 'bootable' can't be an instance attribute.

Still a -1 though as:
- I think there needs to be a warning if the option is used for a driver that doesn't support this method (as its one of a number of options that are otherwise generic)

- Minor nit on with the commit message

- I'd like to see the BP approved first"}, {'account_id': 7494, 'date': '2013-11-24 14:55:08.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 8: I would prefer that you didn't merge this

(1 inline comment)

Do we have other patches for this BP related to left hypervisors? Suggest clarify this in commit log."}, {'account_id': 2835, 'date': '2013-11-25 17:07:34.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 8:

@Phil - Will update commit message to reflect that only a xenapi implementation is provided.

As far as making something like 'bootable' part of the instance model, I have no issue with that, but would prefer not to change that schema here since only one driver implementation will support this initially.  (Others are welcome to add more, of course.)  Either way, there will have to be support for this at the driver layer, so I think this is a nice small step.

@Jay - Not sure what you mean by "left hypervisors."  Others are welcome to contribute driver implementations for other hypversiros.'}, {'account_id': 2835, 'date': '2013-11-25 17:09:16.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 8: (4 inline comments)

commit_message:
Add a driver method to toggle instance booting

Add a driver method to toggle the ability to boot an instance.

The only implementation provided is for the xenapi virt driver.  Other
drivers will log a warning and treat the method as a no-op.

Implements: blueprint cleanup-running-deleted-shutdown

Change-Id: Ie448c681d653b126cb12d3a48d79ab4febde8828

commit_message:
Adding qpid support to cinder

Moving all qpid parameters under default["openstack"]["block-storage"]
["mq"]["qpid"] so that other qpid options can be added under it. Rabbit
parameters will be brought under "mq" eventually. MQ is selected
through default["openstack"]["block-storage"]["mq"]["service_type"].
Default is "rabbitmq".

Implements: blueprint qpid-activemq-support
Change-Id: I4c45a1aa8f6a6a505c8a1494d02f8bf5bc19dbfe

commit_message:
Adding qpid support to glance

Moving all mq related parameters under default["openstack"]["image"]["mq"]
so that other mq options can be added under it. Eventually, all rabbit
options will be brought under it. Bumped up version to 7.1.0

Implements: blueprint qpid-activemq-support

Change-Id: Ie0ed02a9262136c208d88d05f2431ff351e2edb2

commit_message:
Adding qpid support to quantum

Moving all qpid parameters under default["openstack"]["network"]["mq"]["qpid"]
so that other qpid options can be added under it. Rabbit parameters
will be brought under "mq" eventually. MQ is selected through
default["openstack"]["network"]["mq"]["service_type"]. Default is
"rabbitmq".

Implements: blueprint qpid-activemq-support
Change-Id: I7ac232c52d4fcf72764c63562f58f58c1088ef65

commit_message:
Adding qpid support to ceilometer

Moving all qpid parameters under default["openstack"]["metering"]
["mq"]["qpid"] so that other qpid options can be added under it.
Rabbit parameters will be brought under "mq" eventually. MQ is
selected through default["openstack"]["metering"]["mq"]["service_type"].
Default is "rabbitmq".

Implements: blueprint qpid-activemq-support
Change-Id: I4dd153a631063ee7c518e2d49fe01aa39a6f261d

Fixes some testcases where config options were used before they
were guaranteed to be imported. This was causing intermittent
failures of tests such as test_shelve_offload.

Closes-Bug: 1256210

Change-Id: Id0204d67f35cb098a4ddfb670f5968e76b327705
'}]
commit_message:
Fix testcase config option imports

Fixes some testcases where config options were used before they
were guaranteed to be imported. This was causing intermittent
failures of tests such as test_shelve_offload.

Closes-Bug: 1256210

Change-Id: Id0204d67f35cb098a4ddfb670f5968e76b327705

commit_message:
Add HTTP proxy support to ceilometer client

There is a need for HTTP Proxy support in Ceilometer client
It's used in the case when Ceilometer API is not directly available
Proxy url is taken from environment variables http_proxy or https_proxy

Implements: blueprint proxy-support

Change-Id: I839d704a7fa16521292205166d7cbea56497842b

commit_message:
Add a pre-deployment check for volume group allocation

If the default disk allocator doesn't allocate enough space
for all volume groups an error will be raised prior to deployment.

Change-Id: Ie6a971ef000ecf9e9b62f137969d05c119e17af6
Closes-Bug: #1248662

commit_message:
Get oslo-rootwrap config files installed in /etc

Install a default /etc/oslo/rootwrap.conf pointing to an empty
/etc/oslo/rootwrap.d filter definition directory (containing a
.FILTERS placeholder).

We do not mention /usr/share/oslo/rootwrap anymore since we do not
provide this directory by default, but we mention it as a good
packaging practice in the .FILTERS file.

Change-Id: I330216118102107cb31e1b4e7d5318a5c678dd18

commit_message:
Improve timeout for dhcp response waiter

Dhcp checker tool is not always receives info
on dhcp servers in network
To make checking on network with 400 vlans it takes
7 min to perform
Also get_probing_info takes same time for this number of vlans

Change-Id: I03cac773030ccfd6c6f433e117ea9240d787bbbe
Closes-Bug: #1247284

commit_message:
Some network-related code now uses flags from meta

1. Network metadata is now accessible from 'meta' field of NetworkGroup model.
2. Three network metadata flags added.

Flags description: https://etherpad.openstack.org/p/nailgun-network-group-flags

Change-Id: Ia8494c98086b29692b70b0f7a939db2ab91b2dea

commit_message:
Mark rpc,notifier,zmq as Obsolete

Update the MAINTAINERS file to reflect that rpc, notifier, and zmq are
all Obsolete in favor of the oslo.messaging library.

Change-Id: I537688625f4b1d44b82fca35f08e4171341d1ad2

commit_message:
Added resources definition in the pipeline

The 'resources' in the pipeline definition is a list of endpoints for
the pollsters to get the data from. It's optional and it's up to the
specific pollsters to decide how to use it.

The new pipeline definition could be something like the following:

    meters:
        - "*"
    resources:
        - file:///foo/bar/endpoints

Implements: blueprint support-resources-pipeline-item
Change-Id: Ibd7426f8f453c176c99d3786106deb35bbac8d4f

commit_message:
Mark rpc and notifier as Obsolete

See mailing list thread:

  http://lists.openstack.org/pipermail/openstack-dev/2013-November/thread.html#20742

These two packages are in bugfix only mode. New features should be
added to oslo.messaging.

Change-Id: I01711fcdb7f114570b1987910515dceeb3bebe16

commit_message:
Add check for BlockDeviceMappingV2 nova extension

Booting instance from image (creates a volume) option is using
the new BDM format when submitting the create server request to
Nova. Adding a check for Nova extensions if it is supported
before displaying the option.

Change-Id: Ie0b2b5d574babc910e2dac7ce9e3ab6603382ffb
Closes-bug: 1223875

commit_message:
Abstraction of Ceilometer meters information

- Extract the metadata of the meters to a class (label,
  description)
- The list operation support (only, except) filter
- It supports listing meters by their service e.g. .list_nova(),
  .list_neutron()

- Tests for meters list written.

Fixes bug 1226479

Change-Id: Ifa366fd2de3e8f4e31347962630f96344ebba974

I am kind of biased and prefer using inheritance and class/instance scope variables as it is used till now. But the proposed patch has some interesting approach that needs attention(the meta class). In fact - it still relies on the class variables in the child classes. I've proposed some improvements, that I believe perform smoother transition between the old style and the proposed one. Comments welcome."}, {'account_id': 7585, 'date': '2013-10-15 14:31:53.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 4: (1 inline comment)

Thank you very much for the review.

I am not sure, but I am not seeing this class variable approach through the Horizon, just here.

It could be very dangerous to use it this way, the objects then use attributes stored in class, not the object. With combination of something mutable, this could be a problem (there are a few hidden bugs like that)
Also figuring out what is really assigned is messy. Like having that many parameters, that are not actually used, but it rather initialize the object by some side channel(meaning the class attributes.

Objects should be always initialized via init parameters, this is the only clean way people expect, I think.

The metaclass is a compromise. You can define the attrs of the action object in class, so it is somehow a nice DSL for creating of actions. But then you take it and you feed it as parameters to the init method of the object. Also the other approach would require rewriting of all defined actions, that would be a lot of work.'}, {'account_id': 9, 'date': '2013-10-23 06:03:10.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 4:

All horizon/tables/actions.py action classes were rewriten, so there
is standard inicialization of objects, through the parameters of
initializer not through the class variables.
The class variable 'name' stayed though, because it is used for
ordering of the actions in the table. This will be solved in different

commit_message:
The use of the class variables

All horizon/tables/actions.py action classes were rewriten, so there
is standard inicialization of objects, through the parameters of
initializer not through the class variables.
The class variable 'name' stayed though, because it is used for
ordering of the actions in the table. This will be solved in different
bug.

The BaseActionMetaClass has been added, so actions can inherit from
each other and use the class variable DSL in the same time. It is
similar solution to DataTableMetaclass.

Also the bugs with unused or blocking class atributes and [] in
parameters of initializer were solved.

Change-Id: I1b38befe114c1b4781e661a5a127c3f87391e228
Fixes: bug 1182931, bug 1183698, bug 1182908

commit_message:
Add a graduating status for projects

Add an explicit status for projects in the process of graduating
from the incubator, for cases where that is expected to take
enough time that we would need to maintain code in two places
until the graduation is complete.

revisions:
[{'created': '2013-11-01 13:26:38.000000000', 'message': "[PRD-2455] Add more checks to check_networks task

Following checks are implemented now for Nova-Network:

1) +  VLANs of all networks shouldn't be intersected to each other (all network modes) or Fixed VLAN range (VLAN manager).
2) +  IP address spaces of all networks in cluster shouldn't be intersected to each other (exception: Floating ranges can be in Public CIDR).
3) +  IP address ranges inside Public and Floating networks shouldn't be intersected to each other.
4) +  Public ranges should be in one CIDR which calculated by netmask.
5) +  Public network should have a gateway field and it should belong to Public CIDR but should not be in any Public or Floating range.
6) +- Public and Floating networks are rated as a single network when they assigned to nodes' physical interfaces.
      So they must share one VLAN and must be assigned together to one interface.
7) +  Any physical interface of any node can have one assigned untagged network only (exception: point 6).
8)  - All networks should belong to the allowed IP ranges (network of class A, B or C excluding loopback range).
9) +  VLAN IDs shouldn't be out of range 2, 4094. Untagged network should have VLAN ID == None.
10) - Number of Fixed networks should fit in Fixed CIDR and size of one Fixed network.

Change-Id: Ieb4c1666112d8acb0c7413e8c6b09271119703f3

commit_message:
[PRD-2455] Add more checks to check_networks task

Following checks are implemented now for Nova-Network:

1) +  VLANs of all networks shouldn't be intersected to each other (all network modes) or Fixed VLAN range (VLAN manager).
2) +  IP address spaces of all networks in cluster shouldn't be intersected to each other (exception: Floating ranges can be in Public CIDR).
3) +  IP address ranges inside Public and Floating networks shouldn't be intersected to each other.
4) +  Public ranges should be in one CIDR which calculated by netmask.
5) +  Public network should have a gateway field and it should belong to Public CIDR but should not be in any Public or Floating range.
6) +- Public and Floating networks are rated as a single network when they assigned to nodes' physical interfaces.
      So they must share one VLAN and must be assigned together to one interface.
7) +  Any physical interface of any node can have one assigned untagged network only (exception: point 6).
8)  - All networks should belong to the allowed IP ranges (network of class A, B or C excluding loopback range).
9) +  VLAN IDs shouldn't be out of range 2, 4094. Untagged network should have VLAN ID == None.
10) - Number of Fixed networks should fit in Fixed CIDR and size of one Fixed network.

Some error messages are refined and unified.

Change-Id: Ieb4c1666112d8acb0c7413e8c6b09271119703f3

commit_message:
Make merge.py invokable from another script

Until now this script has been used at the command line. Tuskar would like
to consume the merge.py functionality to generate the overcloud heat stack
template. A main() is thus added here as well as a few related nits like
ensuring paths are absolute for included files. The actual merge
functionality is split into its own method so it can be invoked more
cleanly from calling scripts. The main method is then used at the command
line as before

For more info about how this will all be used by Tuskar see
I578b4e9f238590ea245b827bc75d252568d194fe

Change-Id: Ia6b6416fe10358d23f2b120283eecaf4c1178cfd

Remove property decorator in TemplateResource

These methods can do quite a bit of work and treating
them as properties seems a bit odd.

Change-Id: I99cc3c9f74f59f9984daa3e128651926830e9d29

commit_message:
Add ability to configure read access of container

Allow the user to set the container access to private or public.

For public containers, the public URL for accessing it is also provided
to the user.

List containers does not include the metadata of the container. Used ajax
to load the container metadata in the Container table to be able to render
the Container table immediately.

Change-Id: If1e848ad49f522eab8f1b264d54611615481848c
Implements: blueprint swift-container-public-access

commit_message:
Only pass non-None sortby to PrettyTable.get_string

Fixes bug 1256883

Older versions of prettytable are not tolerant to sortby
being provided as an explicit kwarg set to None.

We avoid this issue by leaving the kwarg unspecified when
sorting is not required.

Change-Id: I4ef7bc73a820a63d790a23a0f4e64a1077274d8a

commit_message:
Add OS-QUOTAS API extention: API

Quotas provide the ability to restrict resources for users and projects.
Keystone is used as central quota storage for all components.
All resources and quota limits are stored in keystone. There are
2 types of quotas - per project quotas (project quota) and per user
quotas (user quota). They limit resources for concrete project and user
respectively.

Implementation:

Part 2. API
    Add QuotasExtention router which routes calls related to the
resources
    and quotas.

    Add ResourceV3, ProjectQuotaV3, UserQuotaV3 controllers which are
    responsible for processing operations with resources and quotas.

blueprint: store-quota-data

Change-Id: I106311a6ec3141ad64aac71e0e3ddcd485e01ed2

commit_message:
Do not allow API to expose error stacktrace

Due to specific implementation of RPC error deserialization we have
remote exception traceback built into the error message, therefore
web server puts it to the response and sends to the client. This
patch adds Pecan hook that cuts off traceback from the error message
before it sent to the client.

Closes-Bug: #1244747
Change-Id: Ic12f151123f4ccce36d64608873eeb99eccc525a

commit_message:
Adjust the step in devtest.sh

The step cleanup-env calls virsh, the step install-dependencies
install new version of virsh, which support "--name" option. So
it should run install-dependencies firstly.

commit_message:
Make engine service docstrings conform to Sphinx

This allows our Sphinx-generated documentation to render the
parameters correctly.

There were some errors in some of the "argN"-documented
functions, so I've updated them to include all the parameters.

Change-Id: Ic3b2c7702331bc85744b24434edbb2656c90916a

It's possible to set '@' or ':' character in Linux device name. But
Neutron IP lib doesn't handle correctly these names.

To distinguish VLAN devices from others devices with '@' in their name,

Change-Id: I7ed24ec00f481207d97bdef052f86388f24d9b21

commit_message:
Linux device name can have '@' or ':' characters

It's possible to set '@' or ':' character in Linux device name. But
Neutron IP lib doesn't handle correctly these names.

To distinguish VLAN devices from others devices with '@' in their name,
the details option in iproute2 is used.

Change-Id: I7ed24ec00f481207d97bdef052f86388f24d9b21
Closes-Bug: #1245799
(cherry picked from commit 34f30a1d16d81be86a117690ccc5bdfc5bdd0659)

commit_message:
Fix inconsistency in docs folder

The patch fixes the inconsistency in the structure of the docs/ folder that
appeared in master after a series of merges. The sample/ folder has been
deleted and the only file that resided there has been moved to samples/.

Blueprint rally-docs

Change-Id: I882eac4659bc2c9d11b062538b8f9fd4507aa6ad

commit_message:
VMware: disk management code refector to a single file

extend_virtual_disk moved to disk_util.py
_delete_datastore_file renamed to delete_virtual_disk and
moved to disk_util.py
_copy_vmdk_content renamed to copy_virtual_disk and moved
to disk_util.py

Change-Id: Ia40da9bfa16456da26e0441825f756f901541445

commit_message:
Fix typo in cinder

tranfers -> transfers
recurse -> recursive
satisified -> satisfied

There are other typos will be fixed in Oslo. The commit is:
https://review.openstack.org/#/c/59319/

Change-Id: I6fc2be0414962f456a827d294e258637af665524
Closes-Bug: #1255908

as-is.

commit_message:
Updates .gitignore

To ignore swap files from getting into repository
currently the implemented ignores are *.swp and *.swo
however vim adds more swap files if these files exists,
so improving this with *.sw?

Change-Id: Ie1b458d2b862e6cf2552ae5be6c6178b72e960ab
Closes-Bug: #1255876

commit_message:
Use === and !== instead of == and != in JavaScript.

Fix JavaScript code style to not generate JSHint warnings about the
equality operator.

Change-Id: I1f9f279272e2960eafbaa84aa0ecc7b3b6871775
Implements: blueprint js-coding-style-checks

Hi: thanks for doing this, it's a nice implementation.

The filter implementation looks fine, but I am concerned about the case where the "No Limit" string is generated by your quotainf() and then passed on to further filters.

In particular, the intcomma() and "mb_float_format() filters. Looking at the code for these, it looks like they might not react well to arbitrary string output.

Please make sure you have tested these cases. If you have already and it works, my apologies. Looking at the code, it is not clear this would be the case.

I have tried not to duplicate my comments across files. But they apply to all instances in the html where you apply the filter and the output is piped into another filter.

Thanks!'}, {'account_id': 6610, 'date': '2013-11-18 02:49:54.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 2:

 if settings.USE_L10N and use_l10n:

        else:
            return number_format(value, force_grouping=True)
    orig = force_text(value)
    new = re.sub("^(-?\d+)(\d{3})", '\g<1>,\g<2>', orig)
    if orig == new:

commit_message:
Update artifact name to match documentation

NetBeans uses this property of the pom.xml in the Projects window when
you open the pom.xml as a project, so using a meaningful name greatly
eases navigation.

Change-Id: I209c19a46a66d593d96817d05185c854cecd0b92

commands were to be run.

Additionally, database configuration is done in the 'configuring a
compute node' section, and was duplicated here.

openstack/common/rpc/matchmaker_ring.py:        host = next(self.ring0[key])
 tests/unit/db/sqlalchemy/test_models.py:            r = next(i, None)

What about the two cases above?"}, {'account_id': 6722, 'date': '2013-12-02 04:57:34.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 1:

@Zhongyue

Thanks for your review !
Built-in function next()(not it.next()) was supported from Python 2.6 [1][2]. And six.next was set in six.py as:
    try:
        advance_iterator = next
    except NameError:
        def advance_iterator(it):
            return it.next()
    next = advance_iterator
So both of six.next(it) and built-in function next(it) are okay.

 [1] http://docs.python.org/2/library/functions.html#next
 [2] http://docs.pythonsprints.com/python3_porting/py-porting.html#iterators'}, {'account_id': 3, 'date': '2013-12-02 06:30:31.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 1: No score

commit_message:
Replace data structures' attribute with six module

In Python 3, some data structures' attribute is different in Python 2.
See http://pythonhosted.org/six/#object-model-compatibility
This is change mapping:

   six               Python 2           Python 3
six.next(it)         it.next()          next(it)
six.iterkeys(dict)   dict.iterkeys()    dict.keys()
six.itervalues(dict) dict.itervalues()  dict.values()

Implements: blueprint make-python3-compatible
Change-Id: Ida48f39ff230860feee7305b93b134c625a21663

commit_message:
Add version override support from nova

Nova has a great feature that allows distro packagers to override
version strings by putting config files in known locations. We should
support this in our version processing code, because it's quite handy.

[{'created': '2013-08-22 20:47:01.000000000', 'message': "Make certificate subject RFC-4514 compliant

OpenSSL utilizes a proprietary format for DN's (Distinguished Name). A
certificate subject is the most common use of a DN in X509 but they
appear elsewhere as well. The string representation of a DN has been
standarized for well over a decade. RFC-4514 is the current RFC. All
other crypto libraries and tools use RFC-4514 format, OpenSSL is the
exception. OpenStack should follow internet standards and be capable
of interoperating with other compliant implementations.

This patch does the following:

Changes the existing cert subjects in the documentation and config
files to be RFC-4514 compliant.

Introduces a new module dn_conv.py which is capable of converting
between RFC-4514 DN's and OpenSSL format DN's. dn_conv.py has a
matching unit test, test_dn_conv.py.

Performs a check in openssl.BaseCertificateConfigure to see if the
cert subject is in OpenSSL format, if so a deprecation warning is
emitted. If the subject is RFC-4514 compliant it's converted to
OpenSSL format prior to being passed to OpenSSL.

Adds a dependency on python-ldap to perform DN parsing and
construction. Note, python-ldap was already a testing requirement.

Bug #1214147

Change-Id: Ifcd32bedb7f4e345a73be0fbfdd57e766427f608

commit_message:
Make certificate subject RFC-4514 compliant

OpenSSL utilizes a proprietary format for DN's (Distinguished Name). A
certificate subject is the most common use of a DN in X509 but they
appear elsewhere as well. The string representation of a DN has been
standarized for well over a decade. RFC-4514 is the current RFC. All
other crypto libraries and tools use RFC-4514 format, OpenSSL is the
exception. OpenStack should follow internet standards and be capable
of interoperating with other compliant implementations.

This patch does the following:

Changes the existing cert subjects in the documentation and config
files to be RFC-4514 compliant.

Introduces a new module dn_conv.py which is capable of converting
between RFC-4514 DN's and OpenSSL format DN's. dn_conv.py has a
matching unit test, test_dn_conv.py.

Performs a check in openssl.BaseCertificateConfigure to see if the
cert subject is in OpenSSL format, if so a deprecation warning is
emitted. If the subject is RFC-4514 compliant it's converted to
OpenSSL format prior to being passed to OpenSSL.

Adds a dependency on python-ldap to perform DN parsing and
construction. Note, python-ldap was already a testing requirement.

DocImpact

Fixes: Bug #1214147

Change-Id: Ifcd32bedb7f4e345a73be0fbfdd57e766427f608

commit_message:
Allows users to retrieve ciphered VM passwords

This patch allows users to retrieve VM encrypted passwords using the
`nova get-password` command without specifying the private key.

Change-Id: I13ea132160dca912c6c1643b1006377982b778a1
Implements: blueprint retrieve-ciphered-vm-password

commit_message:
Add missing i18n support

There are some exception messages in common/utils.py and shell.py that
does not support i18n, this patch update the code to support it.

Change-Id: I836b892075333d48e4d1591986fec1362c84fc61
Partial-bug: #1240402

commit_message:
Don't use deprecated module commands

The commands module was deprecated since version 2.6 and it has been
removed in Python 3. Use the subprocess module instead.
See http://docs.python.org/2/library/commands#module-commands

Closes-Bug: #1248216
Change-Id: I0a89dbba374a28b16a6e24f2a1b05ce06e044de4

commit_message:
Improve OVS agent logging for profiling

This patch adds some debug logging statements aimed at profiling
tasks in the agent's main rpc loop.
These logging capabilities will help gain some better insights into
the performance bottlenecks of the agent.

Part of blueprint neutron-tempest-parallel

Change-Id: Ied04b906dbbb9993283981bdee6c96e43a7d19a3

commit_message:
VersionNegotiation - 404 if no version is provided

The version negotiation middleware tries to identify the API version for
a specific url, and then perform routing. It also provides version info
if you attempt to reach "/versions". However, it also returns version
info if you attempt to reach any other endpoint that does not match a
version url.
The version negotiation middleware was modified in order to return all
the available versions of the api only when:
 1- No version is present in the URI and the Accept HTTP Header
 2- The request path is / or /versions
If the version is not provided and the request path is other than the
two mentioned earlier a 404 HTTP Code is returned.
If a version is provided the middleware strips the version from the URI and
pass the request to the next middleware/app.
Added a test suite to ensure that the Version Negotiation Middleware
work as expected.

Change-Id: I1dde1304de60533491790c33db7d2f74d3373722
Closes-Bug: #1251078

(1 inline comment)

You and I discussed this face to face.  I don't know if I really consider this a "clean up" as the new code is equally hard to read.  It does catch and report a wider array of errors.  I suspect that there is a way to restructure these functions that would be clearer.  The inner loop, with all of the continues, should be a stand alone function.  I suspect that, if you worked it right, you could merge the inner functions for both get_endpoints and get_urls into the same inner loop, with one  providing an additional filter on the other.

However, all of this type of cleanup is suspect, as tere is no unit testing for this code.  I could not confirm that your changes had no adverse effect.  Please provide a pre-cursor patch to this one that provides the unit tests, and resubmit this one on top of it.'}, {'account_id': 7191, 'date': '2013-11-18 03:17:35.000000000', 'content': 'Uploaded patch set 2.'}, {'account_id': 3, 'date': '2013-11-18 04:19:13.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 2: Doesn't seem to work

commit_message:
Reorganize Service Catalog

Currently each service catalog call handles it's own parsing and
filtering. Modify this so that each function calls back to another
public function ensuring that filtering and parsing is only handled
once.

This allows us to consolidate some helper methods into the base class
and generally clean up.

Change-Id: I15777436af06baea903182f4b3b5913e2890afd1

(1 inline comment)

I'm not certain that this is the right abstraction.  The name "client" more clearly represents what you want than "session" does.  I think you are creating a new object to try and deprecate bad functions on the old object;  I agree that this cleanup is necessary.

What you really want it, I think, a context object that is used to create components:  proper dependency resolution.  It is the same thing that we are battling on the server.

Values come from sever places:  config file, command line, defaults, and then on a per command basis.  What we have now is a huge dictionary that gets carried around to create them. The logic of what to use to create an object should be separated from where the values come from.

So, session is really just a different shade of lipstick for this particular pig.  There doesn't seem to be a standard DI framework for Python.  The Ceilometer project has started a subproject called Stevedor that might fit here.'}, {'account_id': 9, 'date': '2013-09-20 06:03:10.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 5: Abandoned

commit_message:
Extract a base Session object

A wrapper around a number of connection variables. This will be extended
later with principals such as Kerberos authentication and http sessions.

The intent is that this session object will become the basis for all
other client library communications in OpenStack (as keystone wants to
control things like authentication for everybody).

Change-Id: I8ee728c49d554659d7057ebf17d0f8ceea4d7d8e

[{'created': '2013-11-29 23:38:58.000000000', 'message': 'Fix Neutron Authentication for Metadata Service

A recent change to the way Nova creates a Neutron client
https://review.openstack.org/#/c/52954/4 changed the conditions
under which it re-authenticates using the neutron admin credentials
from "if admin" to "if admin or context.is_admin".  However this
meant that any user with admin role in Nova interacted with Neutron
as a different tenant, preventing them from non-admin actions such
as allocating floating IPS.

This was then addressed by https://review.openstack.org/#/c/56174/4
which only reauthenticated as admin on the explicit use of
"admin=True" parameter to neutonv2.get_client().

However the metadata service does not explicitly create the neutron
client so it has to pass in a context created by
context.get_admin_context() which has is_admin=True but no auth_token.

This change therefore accepts this combination of context values
as a valid reason to re-authenticate as admin, while still allowing
users with the admin role to use their own token.

As a tidy up two tests for getting an admin client are moved from
TestNeutonClient to join the other admin client tests in
TestNeutronClientForAdminScenarios

commit_message:
Fix Neutron Authentication for Metadata Service

A recent change to the way Nova creates a Neutron client
51e5f52e4cb60e266ccde71f205c91eb8c97b48b changed the conditions
under which it re-authenticates using the neutron admin credentials
from "if admin" to "if admin or context.is_admin".  However this
meant that any user with admin role in Nova interacted with Neutron
as a different tenant, preventing them from non-admin actions such
as allocating floating IPS.

This was then addressed by 1c1371c78b990447aeaa4377b512f8887e6ff3ce
which only reauthenticated as admin on the explicit use of
"admin=True" parameter to neutonv2.get_client().

However the metadata service does not explicitly create the neutron
client so it has to pass in a context created by
context.get_admin_context() which has is_admin=True but no auth_token.

This change therefore accepts this combination of context values
as a valid reason to re-authenticate as admin, while still allowing
users with the admin role to use their own token.

As a tidy up two tests for getting an admin client are moved from
TestNeutonClient to join the other admin client tests in
TestNeutronClientForAdminScenarios

Change-Id: Ic2a6f383a85f6bb606d8d65feaefa0d23329adb9
Closes-Bug:  1255577

commit_message:
Revert "Add test_cases for cinder cli in v2 version"

These tests aren't parallel safe, as they make calls into cinder
that assume nothing else is changing the environment, but they
are. This was seen in errors like:

http://logs.openstack.org/43/59243/2/gate/gate-tempest-devstack-vm-postgres-full/e2be8a0/

Doing a full revert as this is currently bouncing a lot of code
that is unrelated. This will need to be rethought in a future
iteration.

This reverts commit cceda7d4c727815aff95d8deb941ffce069f2c8b.

Change-Id: I44ef405695074615ef6447078958791af9b99827

commit_message:
API update: return objects not links

when responding to /<plural>/ return a list of the objects
not a list of links. This is to keep it in line with
how other openstack API work.

part of blueprint api
Change-Id: I355d74323b971b5bd890e075de7fd2bc4d4c7430

it is an admin context.

This is to support some services (metadata API) where
an admin context is used without an auth token.

This fixes an issue introduced in
1c1371c78b990447aeaa4377b512f8887e6ff3ce which broke metadata

Closes-Bug: 1256572
'}]
commit_message:
Fix metadata API neutron V2 requests.

In the case where no auth_token is present
we allow use of neutron admin tenant credentials if
it is an admin context.

This is to support some services (metadata API) where
an admin context is used without an auth token.

This fixes an issue introduced in
1c1371c78b990447aeaa4377b512f8887e6ff3ce which broke metadata
service requests when using the neutron V2 API.

Change-Id: Idc6b8c9e2a52fdbcf9fc58c11f3cdaf7656222d0
Closes-Bug: 1256572

This patch introduces a new parameter to the benchmark config, namely

commit_message:
Run benchmark scenarios for a given period of time

This patch introduces a new parameter to the benchmark config, namely
the "duration" parameter. In case it is used instead of the "times"
parameter in the config, it specifies the period of time (in minutes)
during which the benchmark should be launched over and over (so that
the actual amount of scenario runs gets undefined).

A benchmark config which would launch booting/deleting servers concurrently
from several users/tenants during 5 minutes would then look like this:

"benchmark": {
    "NovaServers.boot_and_delete_server": [
        {"args": {"flavor_id": 1,
                  "image_id": "73257560-c59b-4275-a1ec-ab140e5b9979"},
         "execution": "continuous",
         "config": {"duration": 5, "active_users": 2,
                    "tenants": 3, "users_per_tenant": 2}}
    ]
}

Blueprint flexible-benchmark-config

Change-Id: Ic5085d973abf177077dcabe57b92992e02459370

commit_message:
Moves negative tests from api/compute/keypairs/test_keypairs

This change set seperates negative tests in test_keypairs to a
new negative file test_keypairs_negative.

Note: HACKING.rst
The second requirement is that all negative tests must be added to a negative
test file. If such a file doesn't exist for the particular resource being
tested a new test file should be added

Change-Id: I18f195d8470e6a9a135ee346a3489ba5d553b0a1

commit_message:
All classes should explicitly inherit object class

To avoid pylint errors six.with_metaclass was substituted
with six.add_metaclass and explicit inheritance of object class.

Change-Id: I516f111a9ba1af414b1a5daefad44b743af0412f

Ignore nbactions.xml

This file is a per-user build customization file created by NetBeans,
which is often created for documentation projects to define the
"clean generate-sources" action for easy access in the UI.

commit_message:
Continue to delete volumes that DNE in rbd backend

If a volume has already been deleted in the RBD backend, catch the
exception and let Cinder continue removing it in the database.

Closes-Bug: #1254318
Change-Id: I99b591ce78d82c6eaabff0459d9c523e85c8e65f
(cherry picked from commit 3de7da12d1098ef777305099e5f4a039e536bf99)

[{'created': '2013-11-30 19:43:35.000000000', 'message': "Grant access to 'dash'@'localhost' in dashboard setup

MySQL does not include local socket connection in the '%' wildcard. This
meant that following the existing instructions if the dash was installed
on the same system as the database it was not actually able to access
it.

A grant for 'dash'@'localhost' has been added to address this. It is
worth noting that in this situation (dash + MySQL on same host) this
means that the wildcard grant is actually insecure and not required, but
this is a wider issue that we need to address/highlight  at some point.

Currently we issue both grants for all services, this fix just brings
the dashboard instructions into line with the rest.

Change-Id: Id32432c3612945d6cc8860e947d332d15a8072b4
Closes-Bug: #1255975
backport: havana
(cherry picked from commit 1cad5969600f53f46b948a9ba6f6cd907f033a9c)
"}]
commit_message:
Grant access to 'dash'@'localhost' in dashboard setup

MySQL does not include local socket connection in the '%' wildcard. This
meant that following the existing instructions if the dash was installed
on the same system as the database it was not actually able to access
it.

A grant for 'dash'@'localhost' has been added to address this. It is
worth noting that in this situation (dash + MySQL on same host) this
means that the wildcard grant is actually insecure and not required, but
this is a wider issue that we need to address/highlight  at some point.

Currently we issue both grants for all services, this fix just brings
the dashboard instructions into line with the rest.

Change-Id: Id32432c3612945d6cc8860e947d332d15a8072b4
Closes-Bug: #1255975
backport: havana
(cherry picked from commit 1cad5969600f53f46b948a9ba6f6cd907f033a9c)

commit_message:
Return a descriptive error message for controllers

- A better error message is returned when calling controllers
  with incorrect arguments.
- Real TypeErrors are not bubbled up as 500s

This is based off of a patch by Jeffrey Zhang:
    https://review.openstack.org/#/c/48843/

Co-Authored-By: Lei Zhang<zhang.lei.fly@gmail.com>
Change-Id: I0c043def9c025c18b4cd034640a467586f8cbcfa
Closes-Bug: #1149987

Neutron does work with tenant isolation, just not reliably with the full tempest workload. It basically is acting as a stress test suite for neutron and neutron falls apart. commit_message:
Skip forced tenant isolation qouta tests if running with Neutron

Commit 430dae3 changed the tempest.api.compute.admin.test_quotas tests
to always run with tenant isolation regardless of the setting in
tempest.conf. This does not work if running the tests with Neutron since
Neutron does not currently work with tenant isolation. So this patch
skips the forced isolation quota tests if Neutron is being used.

Closes-Bug: #1248435

Change-Id: I3ca462b4c6266ba1fd76a86011f77fe8a2ddb19a

commit_message:
Remove unused oslo libs

* cfgfilter isn't used
* middleware.debug replaced with log_exchange middleware
* rpc and notifier are both obsolete now, we'll use oslo.messaging lib

Change-Id: I0f04694fdb5eb0c6e4b01e563fb3901af7796f72

reflecting that only the Xen hypervisor currently supports the use of

change.

commit_message:
Updated can_set_mount_point default in docs

The can_set_mount_point default has been changed from True to False,
reflecting that only the Xen hypervisor currently supports the use of
this option. This patch updates the documentation to reflect the
change.

The default changed in commit: d34d7904eed431937b3d75c11da7743767ce9551

Change-Id: I4522718cb7335a1f13557acc0bad1e8f407571ad
Closes-Bug: #1255136

commit_message:
Add volume limits to project overview.

Commit d4b0ab4aa395bf4df2964efcc358100117efdaa0 fixing
bug #1178694 removed volume quotas from project overview.
Cinder is not reporting Snapshot limits today, so that info
can't be added without including quotas again, defeating the
purpose of the original fix.
This fix will only add Volume Qty & Total Storage GB used (including
snapshot size, if any ).
Information is hidden if volume list is empty.

Partial-Bug: #1244875
Change-Id: Ia72e40329ecf08b57fb26cd847f02cececc53579

commit_message:
Grant access to 'dash'@'localhost' in dashboard setup

MySQL does not include local socket connection in the '%' wildcard. This
meant that following the existing instructions if the dash was installed
on the same system as the database it was not actually able to access
it.

A grant for 'dash'@'localhost' has been added to address this. It is
worth noting that in this situation (dash + MySQL on same host) this
means that the wildcard grant is actually insecure and not required, but
this is a wider issue that we need to address/highlight  at some point.

Currently we issue both grants for all services, this fix just brings
the dashboard instructions into line with the rest.

Change-Id: Id32432c3612945d6cc8860e947d332d15a8072b4
Closes-Bug: #1255975
backport: havana

I will +1 this now but just wanted to point out that simply adding a constant to oozie_helper is not really helpful in itself since it is not referenced by config_helper which actually sets the hard coded 1024 default.  If somebody changes the default value that is set in config_helper, the replacement will still not occur.  To protect against this, there should be a constant somewhere with the value of 1024 that is referenced in both places, where the default is set and where the default is replaced.  This way, if the default value is changed in the future, the constant value would be changed and the replacement would still occur as expected.'}, {'account_id': 8411, 'date': '2013-11-22 18:51:49.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 3: Looks good to me, but someone else must approve

Fixes: bug #1243638

[{'created': '2013-10-18 07:35:19.000000000', 'message': 'change status code to 202 on server delete

According to RFC2616 when we return 204 on DELETE request, then we MUST
get 404 in a immediate subsequent request. So 202 is a more accurate
response.

Fixes bug: 1152623

Change-Id: Ib62dcb01850d3db4ccf8345f0704abf8ebe3c867
'}, {'created': '2013-11-18 02:43:32.000000000', 'message': 'change status code to 202 on server delete in v3 api

commit_message:
change status code to 202 on server delete in v3 api

According to RFC2616 when we return 204 on DELETE request, then we MUST
get 404 in a immediate subsequent request. So 202 is a more accurate
response.

Fixes bug: 1152623

Change-Id: Ib62dcb01850d3db4ccf8345f0704abf8ebe3c867

Update openstack/common/policy and rewrite cinder/policy

Port policy from Oslo and update cinder/policy.
Update tests.

Oslo version: 5e765b2546dab9d04e4641d92296bfa3d3b17ebf

commit_message:
remove openvswitch plugin dependency from ovs_lib module

Currently l3 and dhcp agent need to import constants module from
neutron.plugins.openvswitch.commmon even if we are running linuxbridge
plugin alone. This will make l3 and dhcp agent failed to work with
linuxbridge plugin. So we need to remove openvswitch plugin dependency
from ovs_lib module so that l3 and dhcp agent can work with linuxbridge
plugin.

fixes bug: 1248017

Change-Id: Ie8bc198d15fccd5ac3169c8b7f41e588a08b9131

commit_message:
Fixing check order for empty body in get_body()

Cinder API logged the following debug message for each request with
empty body:
"Unrecognized Content-Type provided in request get_body"
Check order was fixed in get_body function to follow the correct flow
and display the right message (empty body).

Change-Id: Ie561983a4da791a412fea3fc390dab718dfce191
Closes-Bug: #1252692

commit_message:
GlusterFS: Ensure Cinder can write to shares

Ensure the Cinder user can write to the GlusterFS share.  This
is required for snapshot functionality, and means the admin
does not have to set this permission manually.

Closes-Bug: #1236966

John,

Let me address your questions:

>>I am curious though if you want to claim DB2 support this needs to run in CI 
Yes, we are planning on claiming support during Icehouse and as part of that are working on getting DB2 into the CI process.  I am not sure if we are going to be able to get it into the current infrastructure or if we it will be a third party (non-voting) job.  We have CI on it working internally, just need to make it available externally.

>>and I'm curious if you could clarify regarding versions of DB2 (free, enterprise etc etc)
We test internally on DB2 Express-C which can be freely downloaded.  We also test on DB2 Enterprise.  Grizzly was working on DB2 10.1.  Havana and Icehouse will require version 10.5.

We are close to getting DB2 support in sqlalchemy-migrate and Matt Riedemann has made good progress getting Nova's changes to support DB2 approved.

For Cinder we will have very little that needs to be changed.  This change, the change to retry DB2 disconnects that is currently abandoned while we wait for Oslo to pick up the base change.  Then I will need to commit changes to get the unit tests working.  Just starting to play around with that now."}, {'account_id': 3, 'date': '2013-11-14 00:23:34.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 2: Works for me

commit_message:
Make volume_glance_metadata_create compat with DB2

As DB2 does not support SQL insert via raw number type if
table column data type is "CLOB" ("TEXT" in sqlalchemy), we need
to convert numerical values to string before insert operations.

This problem was discovered through the
test_volume_create_get_update_delete_from_image test case in
tempest.api.volume.test_volumes_get.  The test case fails with
a DBError without this change in place.

Partial-blueprint db2-database

Change-Id: I5b378cce5b639df23d7003548f49bdab1eecf6a0

commit_message:
Add support for NSX/NVP DHCP services

This is a feature patch (1 of 3) that adds support for DHCP
services provided by the NSX (aka NVP) platform. Green-field
deployments can use the AGENTLESS mode, which will make the
core plugin interact solely with the NSX platform to provide
DHCP services. Support for metadata proxy services, migration
for brown field deployments will be added in future patches.

Partial-implements blueprint nsx-integrated-services

Change-Id: Idfc4b2d871e70cd557d8e0e6b23e5563f9ed3420

commit_message:
Clean up duplicate code in v2.image_data.py

glance/api/v2/image_data.py:ImageDataController.upload has two identical
"except exception.StorageFull as e" clauses. One should be removed.

Fixes bug #1256207

Change-Id: I42fc5126e493591045d09ffb9abbc4816e63ef60

commit_message:
Change ConductorManager to self.db when record cold_migrate event

In conductor manager, when cold migrate an instance, conductor
manager will record event of cold_migrate.

When record this event, conductor manager pass ConductorManager but
not self.db as parameter for compute_utils.EventReporter(), as we
can access the db directly from conductor manager so going through
ConductorManager as a proxy is unnecessary.

Change-Id: Ic52228c2550294c2df37d10d36637e4d0e3a1a30

commit_message:
Bump to sqlalchemy-migrate 0.8.2

This allows us to drop some unsightly
0.7.3 patching and also avoids potential
issues in using 0.8.1 which had a bad
release version string (it was called '0.7.3dev' by mistake).

This will require a requirements change here:

 https://review.openstack.org/56662

Change-Id: I5f80dfc07f8256716d025002fc1a1f47e58b2142
Closes-Bug: 1251700

[{'created': '2013-11-27 19:33:51.000000000', 'message': "Fix for Metadata API fail with Neutron (WORKINPROGRESS)

We need a way to identify a admin context minted by
get_admin_context() so we can use Neutron's credentials in this
case. Note that in this specific case we are calling get_admin_context
in get_metadata_by_address (nova/api/metadata/base.py#L464). This
context is passed down several layers (see stack trace in bug report)
before the time get_client is actually called. At this point the
only information we used to act on was if the admin parameter in
get_client method is true or false. we need to add a check for
the AdminContext from get_admin_context as well in addition to the
admin parameter to pick up and use Neutron credentials

Change-Id: Ibcb0b72c37bd71cff5d420dce21c6c0fb518cbaa
Closes-Bug: 1255577

commit_message:
Fix for Metadata API fail with Neutron (WORKINPROGRESS)

We need a way to identify a admin context minted by
get_admin_context() so we can use Neutron's credentials in this
case. Note that in this specific case we are calling get_admin_context
in get_metadata_by_address (nova/api/metadata/base.py#L464). This
context is passed down several layers (see stack trace in bug report)
before the time get_client is actually called. At this point the
only information we used to act on was if the admin parameter in
get_client method is true or false. we need to add a check for
the AdminContext from get_admin_context as well in addition to the
admin parameter to pick up and use Neutron credentials from nova.conf

Change-Id: Ibcb0b72c37bd71cff5d420dce21c6c0fb518cbaa
Closes-Bug: 1255577

ImagePropertiesFilter but with that came a bug due to a missing format
specifier.

Can you expand on when this is necessary (vs. letting garbage collection handle it)?

Also, are there places in bin/swift or swiftclient/client.py where this should be getting called?'}, {'account_id': 9065, 'date': '2013-10-18 02:20:18.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 1:

We are using swiftclient.client.Connection in a  multi-threaded program, and the program is a daemon. We have hundreds of machines. And we also have several swift accounts for different types of tasks. We found that we always had thousands of connections to the swift server. Then I found that the socket connection will not be closed when a thread is done.
Also, I think a close method is needed by such a Connection, Since sometimes someone need to close it by hand.

I think bin/swift does not need close Connection, because we use it as a simple tool and the connection will be closed when the progress is exited.'}, {'account_id': 2696, 'date': '2013-10-18 21:24:16.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 1: Looks good to me, but someone else must approve

lgtm, but it could use some unit tests, perhaps?'}, {'account_id': 9065, 'date': '2013-10-22 09:09:31.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 1:

Allow a context to be elevated to admin status

The mimics the method included in the oslo.rpc CommonRpcContext, so will
work both at the API and Central layers

The notifier itself doesn't use the configuration. So let's not store
it, that lights the dependency a bit on this configuration object.

Blueprint: messaging-decouple-cfg

Change-Id: Ic4b5ddd93ea0382bd8292f9e31b7dacba9b489d3
"}]
commit_message:
Avoid storing configuration in notifier

The notifier itself doesn't use the configuration. So let's not store
it, that lights the dependency a bit on this configuration object.

Blueprint: messaging-decouple-cfg

Change-Id: Ic4b5ddd93ea0382bd8292f9e31b7dacba9b489d3

commit_message:
There is no sense to keep py33 in tox envs

At least we have eventlet in our deps that couldn't be installed in
Python 3.X env.

commit_message:
Avoid AttributeError with Message object

per @doug's feedback in the bug report. Need to change the code
to delay the translation and the string interpolation until
the log message is actually going to be emitted.

Change-Id: Ifa925a75d7e19164081c80bf6ee418492ae63a73
Closes-Bug: 1242820

commit_message:
Fix duplicate definition and scope in JavaScript

Fix code that makes JSHint issue duplicate definition
and use out of scope warnings.

Change-Id: I5a112a4bfc46b84ce3deb4e58c548aa6d8b8ae54
Implements: blueprint js-coding-style-checks

commit_message:
Fixed Murano Platform tests

Added skip actions for all platform tests when
Open Stack does not meet to the Murano requirements.
This fix allows to resolve all false-negative tests results.

Change-Id: I82e333d94f293cf7bcd39803bb41587fd494074e

Create policy.Enforcer in the request context, so we can use
the same object for policy processing in both the context and
API controller, avoids loading the policy file multiple times
per request, and ensures the same policy definition is used.

blueprint: request-scoping-policy

Change-Id: Ie4589e5e0661c9f06afb0b98fe1120eea07d0b05
'}]
commit_message:
Create policy Enforcer object in context

Create policy.Enforcer in the request context, so we can use
the same object for policy processing in both the context and
API controller, avoids loading the policy file multiple times
per request, and ensures the same policy definition is used.

blueprint: request-scoping-policy

Change-Id: Ie4589e5e0661c9f06afb0b98fe1120eea07d0b05

commit_message:
Fix docstring on detail in glance/api/v1/images.py

"Returns detailed information for all public, available images" is
inappropriate on detail, because the private image can be returned also.

Change-Id: Ib173a6813cb70270866476368ffa1ccbb77047aa
Closes-Bug: #1256217

Enforce keystone service endpoint URL for auth

be used for tenants/tokens ops inside the savanna client.

commit_message:
Fix bug in tests.benchmark.test_utils

Too slow ScenarioTestCase.test_run_scenario_timeout
was fixed by correct settings of 'too_long' method in
FakeScenario and default timeout values in the test,
which led to an increase in the speed of this test.

Change-Id: I5748108e14ddd7639fc792dca2df9fc8829f32f8
Closes-Bug: #1242230

revisions:
[{'created': '2013-11-29 10:56:47.000000000', 'message': 'Revert "Support building wheels (PEP-427)"

This reverts commit 9d460a44e4bd0d777ec41a2dc0be6dc80a01a781.

The patch being reverted should not have been merged, because
setting universal to True is used to claim in-place python 2/3
compatibility in Wheel packages.

We don't support python 3 yet, so we must not claim the opposite
here (as this would harm end users as soon as we start uploading
Wheel packages to PyPi).

Please see the following links for details:
 - http://pythonwheels.com/
 - http://lists.openstack.org/pipermail/openstack-dev/2013-November/020059.html

Change-Id: I73106d2a1752fa8ee11694c6d9c123a953e6c462
'}]
commit_message:
Revert "Support building wheels (PEP-427)"

This reverts commit 9d460a44e4bd0d777ec41a2dc0be6dc80a01a781.

The patch being reverted should not have been merged, because
setting universal to True is used to claim in-place python 2/3
compatibility in Wheel packages.

We don't support python 3 yet, so we must not claim the opposite
here (as this would harm end users as soon as we start uploading
Wheel packages to PyPi).

Please see the following links for details:
 - http://pythonwheels.com/
 - http://lists.openstack.org/pipermail/openstack-dev/2013-November/020059.html

Change-Id: I73106d2a1752fa8ee11694c6d9c123a953e6c462

subject: Support detection of fixed ip already in use
messages:
[{'account_id': 6873, 'date': '2013-11-04 17:44:05.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 1: I would prefer that you didn't merge this

(2 inline comments)

While this works, I'd rather see python-neutronclient changed to distinguish between port limit exceeded and fixed IP already in use so that nova can just catch the different exceptions and handle appropriately rather than put all of this validation logic in nova directly.

I believe that's why bug 1207914 is marked as affecting python-neutronclient also, so the client code can be more robust in error handling from the server so nova can translate the exceptions easier."}, {'account_id': 3, 'date': '2013-11-04 17:57:27.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 1: Works for me
