- check-grenade-devstack-vm http://logs.openstack.org/65/55165/1/check/check-grenade-devstack-vm/e85a025 : SUCCESS in 32m 35s
- gate-devstack-vm-cells http://logs.openstack.org/65/55165/1/check/gate-devstack-vm-cells/8ededf5 : SUCCESS in 8m 48s (non-voting)
- gate-nova-pylint http://logs.openstack.org/65/55165/1/check/gate-nova-pylint/3c23172 : SUCCESS in 11m 17s (non-voting)
'}, {'account_id': 6873, 'date': '2013-11-04 21:08:36.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 1:

Copying my latest comment from the bug report:

OK, so you're getting an IpAddressInUse exception from neutron and the client isn't handling it specifically so it just sends a generic NeutronClientException with the 409 code, I get that.

Looking at the neutron client code, there is a mapping for handling PortInUse specifically:

https://github.com/openstack/python-neutronclient/blob/2.3.1/neutronclient/v2_0/client.py#L51

I think we could easily do the same for IpAddressInUse and then check for that in nova once a version of python-neutronclient is released that contains the new exception class (and nova can require that version).

It would push fixing this out 'the right way' for awhile, which is not fun and might require a workaround in the nova code (with a TODO in there to clean it up).

========================

So I guess I'd be OK with this change if there is a TODO in the code to clean it up once the neutronclient translates the IpAddressInUse error to a specific client exception type that we can handle."}, {'account_id': 6873, 'date': '2013-11-04 22:06:56.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 1:

Drew, I posted a python-neutronclient change here:

https://review.openstack.org/#/c/55190/

So if you add the TODO(thorst) in the code and reference the neutronclient change in your commit message, I'd be OK with this workaround."}, {'account_id': 6873, 'date': '2013-11-04 22:08:45.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 1: (1 inline comment)

'}, {'account_id': 6873, 'date': '2013-11-04 22:12:26.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 1: (1 inline comment)

'}, {'account_id': 1849, 'date': '2013-11-12 03:27:05.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 1: I would prefer that you didn't merge this

(3 inline comments)

looking for some clarifications as to why this doesn't align with the plan outlined in https://bugs.launchpad.net/nova/+bug/1247844"}, {'account_id': 6873, 'date': '2013-11-12 03:54:58.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 1: (2 inline comments)

'}, {'account_id': 1849, 'date': '2013-11-12 18:44:31.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 1: Do not merge

(1 inline comment)

so in gate we use latest trunk for clients, so I don't think a workaround is necessary here, the only gotcha is that we need to make sure we release neutronclient before Icehouse is released which sounds doable to me. So I the correct bug fix should involve https://review.openstack.org/#/c/55190/"}, {'account_id': 9, 'date': '2013-11-20 06:03:05.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 1:

commit_message:
Support detection of fixed ip already in use

When creating the neutron port, several errors may occur due to the
state of the system.  Due to limitations on how those errors are
reported back to nova, it is assumed that in the _create_port method a
409 error is an Port Limit exception.  There are other errors that may
occur however.  One common one is when the user specifies a fixed_ip
address that is already in use.

This change will do a check ahead of time to make sure that a fixed ip
address (if specified) is not already used.  If it is used, it raises
a specific exception rather than an Port Limit exception.  Also
attached is a unit test as well that verifies this path.

Change-Id: Ifae03d431ccdc065eea1dea8532371b47d621d4b
Closes-Bug: #1247844
Related-Bug: #1207914

commit_message:
Fix API exceptions handling for message and error code

API exceptions were not returning correct errorcode.
A bug will be opened for moving these exceptions into climate.api but
for this commit, the idea is just to quickly fix it.

Change-Id: I5563c93dac45e22dc3348f5e380521cf8537b440

commit_message:
Separate samples

This patch renames samples as a task and a deployment samples. Samples
was separated practically by the content. The pronounced samples will
introduced on next patches.

Change-Id: I23805888ec6c4b840ab4db867d7deb39010c2506
Implements: blueprint rally-docs and blueprint independent-deploy

commit_message:
Fix lb-healthmonitor-update to work with correct object

Previously in case specified id was incorrect, client fetched
healthmonitors trying to filter them by name which had no effect since
healthmonitor object doesn't have name attribute.
The patch fixes the behavior by making lb-healthmonitor-update rely
on finding resource by id, not by name-or-id

Change-Id: Iade1c3270ec6c60362dd9a9b5e2ffdb0ad9430c1
Closes-Bug: #1245859

commit_message:
Update completed tasks status to "finished"

After successfully finishing a benchmark task, Rally does not update its
status from "test_tool->benchmarking" to "finished". As a result, these
tasks get incorrectly stored in the database with the "test_tool->benchmarking"
status, which prevents them from being deleted according to user's requests.

The patch also adds the "failed" task status and sets this status in
case of an error occuring in the test engine 'with' block.

Closes-Bug: #1255980
Blueprint independent-deploy

Change-Id: I5088f24feb35459d850ae054a62a0544b765ba40

commit_message:
Tracking deployment status into context on error

An instance of Engine Factory can be used as a context manager to
supervise a status of the deployment on occured errors. Transitions
which are processed:

    (DEPLOY_STARTED | DEPLOY_FINISHED) -> DEPLOY_FAILED
    CLEANUP_STARTED -> CLEANUP_FAILED
    DEPLOY_FINISHED -> DEPLOY_INCONSISTENT

Change-Id: I098865057b8d95ae60a79bd49dc2e5026e5fd87d

commit_message:
Validate file

Update artifact names to match documentation

NetBeans uses this property of the pom.xml in the Projects window when
you open the pom.xml as a project, so using a meaningful name greatly

commit_message:
Updates .gitignore

To ignore swap files from getting into repository
currently the implemented ignore is *.swp
however vim adds more swap files if .swp exists,
so improving this with .*.sw?

Closes-Bug: #1255857

Change-Id: I22b6fa351dd565d4783f432c01785c706acd8397

commit_message:
Fix Storwize terminate_connection with no host

Nova may pass a connector to Cinder with no 'host' field, which was
causing a KeyError in the Storwize driver. This patch resolves this case
by doing the following:
1. If the volume is mapped to only 1 host, unmap it
2. If the volume was not mapped or mapped to multiple hosts, print a
   warning but don't raise an exception

Change-Id: I0ec1c24adbdfbcf1c4868b4981a2e2618d4b411c
Closes-Bug: #1244257

commit_message:
Fix suppressed exceptions for migration downgrade

In SQLAlchemy migration versions 009, 010 and 020, we missed
reraising exceptions while logging errors in case of a downgrade.
We don't want exceptions to pass silently. This patch fixes that.

Closes-bug: 1227881

Change-Id: Id11b1c5d2e26d208e88bb84e5b46c4b7affc3f9f

commit_message:
Fix ambiguity and duplication in network install

As noted in the bug report, the initial paragraph confused where the
commands were to be run.

Additionally, database configuration is done in the 'configuring a
compute node' section, and was duplicated here.

Change-Id: If162d588f1d2c3eb85600c1cc481def9377ce94e
Backport: havana
Closes-Bug: 1256188

commit_message:
Pass the size when fetching image in xenapi driver

In commit 6e287c0f2bb7d4994d50f1763f412277e4dac6f7 the fetch_to_raw
method was changed to accept the volume size so it can fail when the
image doesn't fit in the destination volume. In this commit we also
updated all the volume drivers to pass the volume size to that method so
it could perform the check. The xenapi driver missed that change.

This commit updates the xenapi driver to pass the volume size when
fetching the image to enable the introduced check.

Change-Id: I89bc4b3b1c1e6b06f5c529166cf9ffa1fe600c96
Related-Bug: #1235358
(cherry picked from commit c4db75abddbb72ac5f717f6a9266e078b69206a8)

commit_message:
Fail when image is bigger than the volume

When creating a new volume from a qcow2 image stored in glance, we will
be given the physical size of the image instead of the virtual size.
Most drivers will convert that image to raw after downloading for
resizing it to the requested volume size afterwards.

If the virtual size of the image is bigger than the requested one, the
resulting volume might end up being unusable after the resize even
though the creation went good.

This patch will make the volume creation fail if the virtual size of
the image exceeds the one of the requested volume.

Closes-Bug: #1235358
Change-Id: I254cd9e3acf5d9eb7eb913b37d27a14e97568dec
(cherry picked from commit 6e287c0f2bb7d4994d50f1763f412277e4dac6f7)

commit_message:
Mock the udevadm in the TunnelTestWithMTU test

When running the neutron.tests.unit.openvswitch.test_ovs_tunnel.
TunnelTestWithMTU unit test failure occurs because the udevadm is
timing out waiting on a mock-ed device.

Co-Authored-By: Salvatore Orlando <salv.orlando@gmail.com>

Change-Id: I0e16295be66513c2257831bf62fd6a0c19f3b8a4
Closes-Bug: #1253506

commit_message:
glusterfs: implement {allow,deny}_access

GlusterfsShareDriver:

- Introduced user@host:path syntax for specifying gluster
  shares. The user part remains optional, if not given,
  glusterd is contacted locally (via gluster). If given,
  gluster command is executed via ssh to user@host.

  This is necessary to make share adjustment on a remote
  gluster server

- cut out the share syntax handling and aux utils to class
  GlusterAddress which is instantiated in
  GlusterfsShareDriver.__init__(). It also abstracts away
  having to deal with nuances for composing the command line
  for direct and ssh-wrapped gluster invocation.

Change-Id: Ibeea1040bec1eb2950d438dd355b4ebf6eb56f06

"}, {'account_id': 4463, 'date': '2013-11-23 19:22:28.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 1: I would prefer that you didn't merge this

Thanks for the patch Lin.

Couple of points here:
(1) This patch is great because it is going towards the direction other projects like nova implement policies.

(2) Is there a reason why you picked user_id instead of project_id?

(3) Also I think it is just bigger than deleting images, and can be applied to other operations as well. This patch implies moving towards a new direction for implementing who can operate on an image. Currently we do this enforcement in the code right now. Maybe a blueprint could be submitted for the bigger change?

(4) Finally I agree with Servgey, could you please add tests?"}, {'account_id': 6484, 'date': '2013-11-24 13:15:10.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 1: Do not merge

Thanks for working on this. I think this change is managing the operations permission more fine-grained. But I would like to stop merging this.

1. As iccha said, this is a big change for current policy mechanism. So it would be nice if it can be tracked by a blueprint instead of bug.

2. Could you please share the user scenario why you need this? Because generally, user should be belongs to a tenant and we can create policy against tenatnt/project. Though I totally understand we really need a user level policy.'}, {'account_id': 9206, 'date': '2013-11-25 02:56:26.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 1:

Thanks for your response.

In our case, there are many people in a tenant as a member. User can take an instance snapshot for backup the image. And the image will be store in glance service. But in glance, other user which is the same tenant member can also delete the image. We think this may be a problem that if my backup image could be deleted by other.

So, extended this idea to the general image. We think it doesn’t make sense that if i upload an image to glance, but other member can delete or modify it. So, we want to define that only the user(match project_id and user_id) or “project admin” can modify or delete it.

I think this patch is just an emergency treatment for our project. It could not solve all policy request. It needs more comprehensive consideration for all operations.

thanks for you guys, this remind me more thing need to consider.

I will abandon this commit. So, if we want this function work in the future, what i need to do? Register a blueprint?
Thanks you for answering my question.'}, {'account_id': 6484, 'date': '2013-11-25 05:10:41.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 1:

Yep, please create a blueprint and redesign it. I'm glad to review it and hope it can be merged in Icehouse. Thanks again for contributing Glance."}, {'account_id': 9206, 'date': '2013-11-29 06:25:47.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 1: Abandoned'}]

commit_message:
Enhance policy checking, define only image creator can delete the image

For now, admin could not setting the only creator can delete the
image, because it didn't pass the properties to policy module.

This commit is about enhance the delete action policy checking.
If admin want to set the policy like
        "delete_image": "user_id:%(user_id)s"
It will work now.

Change-Id: I43a7d22d86a6b381ee8b251f66c4e3cf27e81c4e
Closes-Bug: #1253963

commit_message:
Make sphinx builders configurable in LocalBuildDoc

Sphinx builders were hard coded to be html and man in LocalBuildDoc
before. This enables users to config a list of builders in setup.cfg
as a comma seperated list, e.g. html,man,doctest

Change-Id: I3528b208c7e719286fe8816acf65f8efdc5844c6

commit_message:
Enable wheel processing in the tests

In advance of enabling wheel processing in pbr overall, enable it
in the integration testing.

Change-Id: Ide460e000c872902590726639d42a5ecac9e4673

'}, {'account_id': 9267, 'date': '2013-11-13 14:56:58.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 1:

I have looked in the logs produced by Jenkins.
Test cases fails due to file permission issues.
IOError: [Errno 13] Permission denied: '/opt/stack/new/data/tempest/tempest-availability_zone'

This error message show that my correction is active, the data directory in in right place ${DEST}/data. Without patch the data dir was in /opt/stack/data.

I have not find information in the logs that explain why we see this. In my test environment (Ubuntu on Virtualbox) I see no file permissions problem.
And same tempest test cases are sucessfull in my local environment.

-rw-rw-r-- 1 xrsjolu xrsjolu 0 nov 13 12:48 /opt/stack/new/data/tempest/tempest-availability_zone

nosetests -v api/compute/admin/  &>/home/xrsjolu/test.log

cat test.log
..
..
tempest.api.compute.admin.test_aggregates.AggregatesAdminTestJSON.test_aggregate_add_host_create_server_with_az[gate] ... ok
..
...

The changes in the devstack installtion scripts just make sure that DEST and DATA variables are handled correct and should not give these type of problem, but I must miss something ?!.
Anyone please help, I am stucked."}, {'account_id': 9267, 'date': '2013-11-14 13:56:28.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 1:

I have find the possible root cause why some test cases fails.
In stack.sh the script change the file permission on the $DEST directory recursively after creation. 

This is not done for the $DATA_DIR directory. This is not needed on my environment. But for other environment with a different default umask this might be necessary. 

I will add the line below after the creation of $DATA_DIR and try again. 

safe_chmod 0755 $DATA_DIR

Note! when I change umask on my test environment with:
umask u=rwx,g=r,o=rx

Same tempest test failed om my environment. And the change in stack.sh mentioned above fixed this.'}, {'account_id': 9267, 'date': '2013-11-15 07:21:58.000000000', 'content': 'Uploaded patch set 2.'}, {'account_id': 3, 'date': '2013-11-15 07:55:24.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 2: Doesn't seem to work

Sad is that I can not reproduce this issue, so all possible ideas for solution I have to push up to Gerrit for test.

commit_message:
Devstack installation scripts are modified to handle variables
$DEST and $DATA_DIR correct. This is needed for Openstack
installations outside the default installation directory.

Closes-Bug: 1239684
Change-Id: I2e80334a680b1ad334b9b341200358baea697e30

commit_message:
add some negative tests for attach volumes

add two negative tests for attach volumes API.
The one is to attach volume to an instance and a host simultaneously,
other is to attach volume with invalid mode.

commit_message:
Integration of run_tests.sh and venv

    - This patch perform an integration of Horizon development
environment.
    - The script run_tests.sh has the same functionnality as Horizon.
    - Documentation generation has to be fix in another patch.
    - A manage.py file has been added to allow the use of some
Django features.

Fixes bug #1229607

Change-Id: I2c493f352cf04ced4bb2ae0b8ec8ba011f019cae

On another note I have tests for verifying scenarios a bit more convoluted such as VM connectivity across routers, and external gateway connectivity with and without nat. are not reachable, connectivity will be checked verifying if an

commit_message:
Enable tenant connectivity check over unreachable nets

For enabling tenant network connectivity checks when tenant networks
are not reachable, connectivity will be checked verifying between two
logical ports on the same network.

This patch adds a new check which uses the instance booted for
verifying public connectivity to ping the port belonging to the dhcp
agent for that network, which must exist at this stage. This is
tantamount to verifying connectivity between two instances on
the same network.

The newly added check is executed only when tenant networks are
not reachable, therefore not disrupting the 'classical' way of
performing tenant connectivity checks.

Closes-Bug #1226158

Change-Id: Id3411101d2c45397ecb0ce5280e4d30fe75f885e

bp v3-api

commit_message:
WIP: Add v3 ServerManager

This is part of a chain of commits that I was working on for
the v3 api.  I'm no longer going to have time to finish that
work, so I'm pushing my changes thus far in case they would be
useful to someone else.

A lot of the client code can be shared between 1_1 and 3, but a
few functions need to change.  This change adds a v3 version of
the ServerManager that inherits from the 1_1 version to avoid
duplicating all of the shared code.

WIP because I expect more changes to be necessary, but I haven't
tested everything yet.

bp v3-api

Change-Id: I235897e7f4ab5966b0263ed70daf5448630553e0

commit_message:
WIP: Remap attributes for nova list

This is part of a chain of commits that I was working on for
the v3 api.  I'm no longer going to have time to finish that
work, so I'm pushing my changes thus far in case they would be
useful to someone else.

The 'nova list' command maps some attributes to shorter names for
convenience.  The long names changed in v3 so this mapping needs
to change.

bp v3-api

Change-Id: I9e74d2fbfa95515e39be55268b7842346a2c190e

revisions:
[{'created': '2013-11-13 20:51:17.000000000', 'message': 'VMware: bug in rebooting powered off instance

Current driver code presumes that you should fail to reboot
if an instance is powered off. Current nova user guides and
other hypervisors implement a "Hard Reboot" if the power
status of the machine is not in "power on" state.

This change makes the vSphere drivers match behaviors with
the other hypervisors.

Change-Id: I5ed19c9bbc2be61d6aaaab05533086893b44f966
Closes-Bug: #1250680
'}]
commit_message:
VMware: bug in rebooting powered off instance

Current driver code presumes that you should fail to reboot
if an instance is powered off. Current nova user guides and
other hypervisors implement a "Hard Reboot" if the power
status of the machine is not in "power on" state.

This change makes the vSphere drivers match behaviors with
the other hypervisors.

Change-Id: I5ed19c9bbc2be61d6aaaab05533086893b44f966
Closes-Bug: #1250680

commit_message:
Adds support for passing extra tenant attributes to keystoneclient

    Patch adds simple kwargs passthrough to tenant update and create
    methods allowing users to exercise the extras functionality
    of keystone.

    As-per keystone data model docs:
    http://docs.openstack.org/developer/keystone/architecture.html#data-model

    Fixes: bug #1220790

Change-Id: Ie02c9b5ae5fc4ec394e98d284c5c8516c73e04c3

commit_message:
Add chance weigher to scheduler

Adds chance weigher to scheduler to allow distribution of requests
randomly between a number of volume managers.

Change-Id: I3f652caf200c406965b52b94cebb244d3bc1779a

commit_message:
Updates .gitignore

To ignore swap files from getting into repository
currently the implemented ignore is *.swp
however vim adds more swap files if these files exists,
so improving this with *.sw?

Change-Id: Ib2f1f6c6a40284ec6ca4a088bad5decd0be842a8
Closes-Bug: #1255876

commit_message:
Improve Cinder Backup support

In my last commit on Cinder module, I add cinder::backup::swift
without adding cinder::backup class which is useful to ensure that
package is installed and service is running.
It also includes variables related to backup configuration.

Note: swift is one of the drivers of backup in Cinder, other ones should
be included in manifests/backup/<driver>.pp

Change-Id: I1a55245abe61f9bbd71568d76ed00e0ecf08307e
Signed-off-by: Emilien Macchi <emilien.macchi@enovance.com>

commit_message:
port test_hypervisor into nova v3 part1

This changeset only copies the v2 files into the appropriate v3
directories unchanged. This is being tried in order to make
reviewing of the porting easier as gerrit will display only what
is actually changed for v3 rather than entirely new files.

Partially implements blueprint nova-v3-api-tests

Change-Id: Iceb6bbde5901325cc5948f61b9b765f635434629

commit_message:
Updates .gitignore

To ignore swap files from getting into repository
currently the implemented ignore is *.swp
however vim adds more swap files if these files exists,
so improving this with *.sw?

Change-Id: I48846345de6838735d2d2e46328698f6a526f397
Closes-Bug: #1255876

commit_message:
Fix confusing use of ! and = in JavaScript

Fix code that makes JSHint issue the confusing use of ! and
assignment used as condition warnings.

Change-Id: Ifa0cdde7f9ce1ca0f4e806dc18d93eb3099914c8
Implements: blueprint js-coding-style-checks

commit_message:
Document neutron-ovs-cleanup

Adds some documentation about the need to run neutron-ovs-cleanup
to ensure that DHCP agent and L3 agent perform properly on reboot.

Closes-Bug: 1156861

Change-Id: I556a15bd2aed18513a57eced465476181097e01d
backport: havana

commit_message:
Avoid loading policy when processing rpc requests

When Neutron server is restarted in the environment where multiple agents
are sending rpc requests to Neutron, it causes loading of policy.json
before API extensions are loaded. That causes different policy check
failures later on.
This patch avoids loading policy when creating a Context in rpc layer.

Change-Id: I66212baa937ec1457e0d284b5445de5243a8931f
Partial-Bug: 1254555

commit_message:
Fix random unit-test failure for NVP advanced plugin

Two problems were observed:
1. Tasks are not scheduled as desired in greenthread. The fix is to
   increase the max status probing time from 1 second to 10 seconds.
2. An error message is show in unit-test log output. Turns out in
   addition to a bug that may cause task manager stop prematurely,
   another unit-test case test_vcns_driver can cause same error
   message being displayed in the log.

Change-Id: I697dd8fc509308108ff1f40400f36ac6271bf4bb
Close-Bug: 1245698

commit_message:
Automatically verify sample config is up to date

Update the pep8 test job to run the script that verifies that the sample
config file is up to date.  If an option is added, changed, or removed,
but the sample config is not updated, tests will now fail.

Change-Id: I9e396af910e670c164407d9dc244e16850d07a0e

commit_message:
Add config up-to-date check script

Add a script that will determine if the sample config file is up to date
with the latest code in the source tree.  Running this automatically in
the gate will prevent patches from going in that didn't update the
sample config when they should have.

Change-Id: I3cdc3480a0947d78165172c1a720e7ef9c1fb144

commit_message:
Do not add DHCP info to subnet if DHCP is disabled

Currently the midonet plugin will add default DHCP information to
each subnet even if the subnet is configured to have DHCP disabled.
This change addresses this by checking the DHCP settings while
creating a subnet, and only adding DHCP information if DHCP is
enabled.

Closes-bug #1230073

Change-Id: I2c422866c60f505df30bfa18bfe8d03599665b7a

commit_message:
Add test_handle_router_snat_rules_add_rules

Add a unit test to verify that snat rules are added and added in order.
So that it could be refactored without fear next time.

Closes-Bug: #1222660
Change-Id: I07e820cc28c9a6c139a8eed0917aef2cfe62638a

commit_message:
Rebind allowed address pairs only if they changed

This patch ensures allowed address pairs bindings are refreshed
only when they actually change.
This will also avoid sending a notification to the agent if no
change actually occured.

Closes-Bug: #1255145
Partial blueprint neutron-tempest-parallel

Change-Id: Iac2502586a0d215a29194590c16c2e1a064f943b

commit_message:
Recommend using the stack user to ssh to the seed

We currently recommend using root to ssh to the seed, but using the
stack user works just fine too since the stackuser element will copy
your SSH key if the local-config element is enabled.

I think it's better to recommend people use the stack user because at
least that same user will work on the undercloud and overcloud, even
if it requires a password in those cases.

Basically, I'm finding myself randomly trying root, stack and heat-admin
and struggling to remember which user is appropriate for each node.

Change-Id: Iddeb47ebce6d0d14f2d2327724e288afe5f1e71d
